HEADWORD: Fattish
<hw>Fat"tish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Somewhat fat;
inclined to fatness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Coleridge, a puffy, anxious, obstructed-looking,
<qex>fattish</qex> old man.</q> <rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>fattism</ent>⟦br⟧
